            </tr>
          </tbody>
        </table>
        <p style="font-family:var(--sans); font-size:13px; color:var(--muted);">Contractor cost estimates reflect typical US market rates for garage cabinetry as of 2026. Individual quotes vary by region and scope.</p>

        <h2>What's in Every Klovo Set</h2>
        <p>Every pre-designed Klovo set ships as a complete package:</p>
        <ul>
          <li><strong>Cabinet boxes</strong> — base and wall cabinet panels with GlideLock connectors pre-installed</li>
          <li><strong>Fixed shelves</strong> — dado-jointed with steel support pins (500 lbs per cabinet capacity)</li>
          <li><strong>Soft-close hinges</strong> on all door cabinets</li>
          <li><strong>Push-to-open ball-bearing drawer glides</strong> (99 lb rated) on all drawer units</li>
          <li><strong>Worktop</strong> — integrated surface top for workbench area</li>
          <li><strong>Wall mounting rail</strong> — continuous rail system for leveled, adjustable hanging</li>
          <li><strong>Trim pieces</strong> — filler strips and crown caps for a finished look</li>
          <li><strong>All fasteners</strong> — everything needed for assembly and wall mounting</li>
        </ul>
        <p>Door kits (for open-shelf configurations) and additional worktop sections are available separately.</p>

        <h2>Build Quality: Why It Matters in a Garage</h2>
        <p>Garages are harder on cabinetry than any other room in the house. Temperature swings from below freezing to 100°F+ cause lesser materials to expand, warp, and delaminate. Humidity from damp cars, rain, and seasonal changes accelerates rust on metal hardware and swelling on unprotected wood edges. Most "garage cabinets" sold at big-box stores are not engineered for these conditions — they're indoor-grade storage with a painted finish applied as an afterthought.</p>
        <p>Klovo's approach starts with the right substrate: moisture-resistant engineered wood panels with a thermally fused laminate (TFL) finish. TFL is the same surface technology used in commercial kitchen cabinetry — it's heat-pressed at the manufacturing stage, not applied as a top coat, which makes it far more resistant to moisture penetration. Every panel edge is sealed with 1&nbsp;mm PVC banding to eliminate the raw edge that would otherwise act as a moisture entry point.</p>

        <h2>Frequently Asked Questions</h2>

        <h3>Are Klovo garage cabinets truly DIY-friendly?</h3>
        <p>Yes. Klovo's patent-pending GlideLock system was designed specifically for homeowners who have never installed cabinets before. Panels are precision-drilled to fit together in only one configuration — there's no way to put them together wrong. The only tool required is a screwdriver for the four back-panel screws at the end of each cabinet. No cam locks to strip, no Allen keys, no guesswork.</p>

        <h3>How long does it take to install Klovo garage cabinets?</h3>
        <p>Each cabinet box assembles in about 2–3 minutes. A full 8-foot set (4–5 cabinets) typically takes less than 1 hour for most homeowners, including wall mounting. The GlideLock connection itself snaps in seconds per panel — the remaining time is measuring, leveling, and securing to the wall.</p>

        <h3>What is the weight capacity of Klovo garage cabinets?</h3>
        <p>500 lbs per cabinet. This capacity comes from dado-jointed shelf construction with steel support pins, not the panel material alone. Drawer glides are rated to 99 lbs push-to-open.</p>

        <h3>What tools do I need to install Klovo garage cabinets?</h3>
        <p>Assembly is almost tool-free. Panels lock together by hand via the GlideLock system. You will need a screwdriver (or drill) to drive four screws through the back panel runners to finish each cabinet box, plus a standard level and stud finder for wall mounting.</p>

        <h3>What size garage cabinet system do I need?</h3>
        <p>Measure your available wall space in linear feet. A typical 1-car garage comfortably fits 6–8 feet of cabinets along one wall. A 2-car garage usually has room for 12–16 feet. Klovo offers pre-designed sets from 6 feet to 20 feet wide, and the modular system lets you start small and expand later without replacing what you already have.</p>

        <h3>Are engineered wood garage cabinets as durable as steel?</h3>
        <p>Klovo's moisture-resistant engineered wood with TFL finish and 1&nbsp;mm PVC edge banding resists humidity and temperature swings common in garages. Unlike steel, it won't rust, dent from tools, or transmit cold in winter. The 500 lbs per cabinet capacity matches or exceeds most steel alternatives.</p>

        <h3>Can I expand Klovo cabinets later?</h3>
        <p>Yes. Klovo is designed around modular expansion. Every cabinet, door kit, and worktop is sold individually. Start with a 6-foot set and add more cabinets anytime — the GlideLock system ensures new additions match the existing installation perfectly in both fit and finish.</p>

        <h3>How much do Klovo DIY garage cabinets cost compared to hiring a contractor?</h3>
        <p>Contractor-installed custom garage cabinetry typically costs $5,000–$15,000+ depending on garage size and material choice. Klovo complete sets range from approximately $1,052 to $7,216 — with zero installation labor cost. Most homeowners save $3,000–$10,000 over a professional build.</p>

        <h3>Where are Klovo cabinets made?</h3>
        <p>Klovo cabinets are manufactured in Georgia, USA, with 20+ years of cabinet-building expertise behind the product line.</p>

        <h2>Ready to Build?</h2>
        <p>Start with your wall measurement and browse Klovo's pre-designed sets. Each listing shows the full cabinet count, configuration, and dimensions so you can plan your space before ordering.</p>
